Chicken Marsala with Fettuccine
Tender chicken breast with sauteed baby bell mushrooms cooked in a combination of rich stock
and Marsala wine then tossed with freshly made fettuccine pasta
Roasted Tomato Basil Soup
Chicken Piccata with Fettuccine
Starting with chicken breast that has been sauteed until succulent in a delicious sauce made with
butter, white wine and capers then sliced and tossed in our freshly made fettuccine pasta
Cheesecake
This is a cheesecake like no other, with a soft cream mix that’s perfectly formed to create a sinfully
delicate texture, it’s the best made-from-scratch cheesecake you will ever have!
A blend of melty parmesan cheese and roasted vegetables baked
into a pillowy dough until gloden and flaky. Topped with garden
fresh herbs and finished with a pinch of sea salt, these appetizers
are certainly a crowd-pleasers
This cozy staple begins with fresh tomatoes and finishes with fragrant
sweet basil; cooked to perfection, it’s blended silky smooth, and full of
scrumptious savory flavor.
Angel Hair Pasta A Modo Mio
Choose your own adventure with your choice of a hearty red, or a tangy rose, or a velvety white
sauce, whichever your selection it gets tossed in with freshly prepared veggies and our signature
made-to-order hand-cut Angel Hair pasta. Anyway you create it you are sure to have an impeccable
vegetarian dish
Roasted Lamb Lasagna
Lamb is the quintessential star at an Italian Easter Sunday dinner. As per tradition, Chef Tony has
created something special by highlighting the succulent flavor of a beautiful Lamb shoulder. Slowly
roasted and used to layer into a classic four-cheese lasagna.The combination of flawlessly cooked
lamb, pasta, and cheese here is so incredibly good you’ll crave it all year round.
Cannoli Cake
Light and airy double-layered sponge cake between a traditional cannoli cheese filling iced with
sweet buttercream frosting and sprinkled with tiny morsels of chocolate.
